The custom kernel-safe rtapi_vsnprintf (and rtapi_vsnprintf.h) is removed: gomc
is uspace-only and uses libc's vsnprintf.  This test validated that custom
float-formatting implementation, which no longer exists.  rtapi_print /
rtapi_print_msg remain, but the actual formatting is now libc's (well-tested;
not gomc's to re-test), so there is no meaningful re-expression.
